</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I like the idea except for adding classes into the equation. I don't think a human Paladin should be any more/less able to take a fireball than a human Rogue for example. It would be something else for the Dev team to figure into the racial balance though... And the skill would be nice if the cap was very low...

<P>-OR-
<P>Make armor the deciding factor. Say a Plate greaves give you a 2% resistance, Chain greaves give 1.5%, etc. Add up all the bonuses from everything you wear and theres you Magic Resistance. Maybe?
<P>-OR-
<P>You could recieve a flat 2% magic resistance per level. When attacked with magic you would subtract the casters level from your total. Lower/higher numbers could be used in all examples of course..
<P>-OR-
<P>You could totally disregard everything I say because it's getting late and I'm tired.
<P>Agiel
